The paper discusses the concept of context in data management, which is a core topic in the database community (cs.DB). The paper also proposes a framework for data quality assessment, which involves machine learning techniques (cs.AI) and optimization (cs.LG). The use of alternative clean versions of data and the optimization of access to external data sources are also relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR) and software engineering (cs.SE).
